comments:
Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Llanaber in Barmouth 
    Urban District. See also Table 2, note (d).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Dolgelly. See 
    also Table 2, note (d).

Created 1894 from the Montgomeryshire part of the parish of Mallwyd. 
    See also Table 2, note (b).

That part which until 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of Llanenddwyn. 
    See also Table 2, note (c).

In 1894 the part in Montgomeryshire became 
    the  parish of Caerinion Fechan, so that thereafter Mallwyd was entirely 
    in Merionethshire. See also Table 2, note (d).
